# Commerce Readiness Standards

Current flow:
- Inquiry-first for complex custom work.
- Consultation-first for weddingwear.
- Quote/payment-link flow later.
- Full checkout can come later for simpler custom shirts/trousers.

Do not implement fake checkout unless explicitly requested.

The system should be ready for:
- Quote creation
- Payment links
- Deposits
- Order status tracking
- Customer measurement profiles
- Uploaded references
- Manual review before production
- Delivery/tracking updates
- Alteration support

Need-by date standard:
- Every custom form should capture needByDate where relevant.
- Weddingwear must capture eventDate and needByDate.
- Urgent/event orders should not be automatically promised.

Policy page standard:
The site must include or be ready for:
- Terms and Conditions
- Privacy Policy
- Delivery Policy
- Returns and Alterations Policy
- Contact page

Operational note:
Even if marketing avoids origin-heavy language, future international commerce may require backend product origin, HS codes, duties/taxes, and shipment metadata.
